author: Phil Helsel
title: Paterson, N.J., mayor tests positive
description: Andre Sayegh, the mayor of Paterson, New Jersey, said Tuesday that he has tested positive for COVID-19. The mayor said he does not have a fever or cough, but is quarantining at home and he encourages people to take the virus seriously.
content:
The mayor of Paterson, New Jersey, Andre Sayegh, says he has tested positive for COVID-19.
